.TH hsh 1 "may 2020" "1.0" "hsh - Simple Shell General Commands Manual"
.SH NAME
hsh - Simple Shell
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.I [OPTIONS] [FILE]
.B Interactive mode
.I [command_name][option_name][argument ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The simple shell takes input commands from the terminal directing them to the operating system to execute action. The interactive shell prompts before each command, possibly with arguments that it also inspects, execute them and handles possible errors. The simple shell reads input in terms of lines from a file and breaks it up into words at whitespaces. 
.SH EXAMPLES
$ ./hsh
 simple@shell $ /bin/ls
 README.md exec.c main.h main.c prompt.c
 simple@shell $
 simple@shell $ exit
 $
.PP
 $ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
 README.md exec.c main.h main.c prompt.c
 $
.SH SEE ALSO
sh(1)
.SH BUGS
There possibly are some bugs as it does not include the full functionality of a shell
